transcript.sentence: Two hands, pick up a square blank piece of white paper.
The Top left corner is brought to the bottom right corner and folded along the diagonal.
The crease is reinforced using the pointer finger of the left hand,
and as unfolded back to a square,
the Top right corner is brought to the bottom left corner and folded along the diagonal.
The crease is reinforced using the pointer finger of the right hand,
and is unfolded
back to a square.
The bottom left corner is folded to the center point, creating a new diagonal across the bottom left corner,
and is kept in this crease position.
The Top left corner is folded to the center point,
creating a new diagonal across the Top left corner, and is kept in this crease position.
The Top right corner is folded to the center point, creating a new diagonal across the Top right corner,
and is kept in this position.
The bottom right corner is folded to the center point, creating a new diagonal across the bottom right corner, and is kept in this position.
The hands move the paper to show that it has now been folded into a smaller square
with edges that form an x shape.
And for cris as that form a t shape,
The left hand finds the left side of the square and proceeds to the right to the triangular tip.
The fingers lift the triangular tip
and unfold it outwards so that the triangular tip now faces the left.
The paper is now made up of a large center square
and a triangle that is pointing outwards to the left.
It looks like an open envelope
opening to the left.
The point of the left hand triangle is brought to the right to meet the first vertical crease,
the left thumb
reinforces the new vertical crease.
The hands lift up the leftmost edge and fold it back into its original square position.
In this square, there is now a smaller triangular cutout
left of the center.
The right hand finds the right side of the square and proceeds left to the triangular tip located at the center.
The right hand picks up the tip and moves it to the right so that it passes the right edge. And about half of the new triangle extends past the right edge.
The left hand creates a crease that is parallel with the vertical crease of the square.
The paper is now folded in half by bringing the Top edge of the square down to the bottom edge.
The left thumb is used to reenforce the fold.
The paper is now made up of a rectangle with a small triangle emerging from between the fold
in the Top right corner.
Use the folded rectangle with the opening, facing the bottom as a guide for the next steps.

Hands open the folded rectangle enough to find the triangular tip on the inside of the fold. The triangular tip is unfolded in the paper, is once again sold it back to its beginning rectangular shape resembling an envelope

with the point pointing downwards. The point of this bottommost triangle is brought in the direction of the Top right corner and folded along the diagonal, creating a new diagonal that reaches from the Top left corner to the bottom right corner.
The left thumb is used to reinforce the fold. The triangular point is then folded back down in the direction of the bottom left corner
on its original crease.
The paper is flipped over once along its left edge.
The paper now appears to be a rectangle with a triangle on the Top and left sides.

The bottom right corner is picked up and lined up to match the triangular point that extends from the Top of the rectangle before kris ing. The left hand follows the left diagonal edge of the piece being folded from the Top right to the bottom left corner.
Using the thumb, the left hand lifts the triangle section of the paper, making sure it does not get folded into the crease.
After the triangle section has been lifted out, both hands reinforce the current fold and move across the edges of the paper, strongly reinforcing all folds and edges.
The paper is positioned such that at the bottom side is a straight edge.
The right side has an elongated triangle pointing outwards to the right.
The left side has a smaller triangle near the Top, pointing to the left.
and the Top side has a small straight edge near the right side, with a diagonal fold
starting from the center
and reaching up towards the Top left corner.
The left hand locates the leftmost point of the left side.
At this point, both hands unfold the tip of the point from the bottom.
The hands pull out a fold that is about a fingernails length inward. From the left point,
this edge is pulled out,
and folded along the diagonal
from the left point to the bottom. Right?
The fold is reinforced.
This will now resemble another small left side facing triangle
at the tip of the larger left side triangle.
The dog is now Complete.
The hands placed the completed origami dog down on the table.
The left side of the origami dog resembles the triangular peak with the small triangle fold
at its leftmost base.
This is the head for the origami dog.
The right most side of the origami dog
is a tail made up of a small triangle
whose diagonal bass starts about midway from the rectangular body and proceeds upward to the right.
The hands grab a black marker and draws a dot at the leftmost point of the triangle, composing the dog's head
and makes a nose.
A second black dot is drawn as the eye by following the diagonal up from the nose and moving inwards
to the right, approximately one fingernail length.
The dog is flipped over along its vertical edge and is currently facing right?
The nose and I are replicated
on this side.
Video ends with the same dedication appearing in the upper left hand corner
to my sweetheart.
The image pauses on six origami dogs, white, yellow, blue,
orange, pink, and grain of differing sizes.
A spinning yellow and pink flower graphic crosses the screen with the word cute
in all capitals being shown.
Another spinning yellow and pink flower graphic approaches the screen with the words best wishes,
images of blue hearts move in the background
to light blue rectangular shapes looking like ribbons with white poker. Dots intersect.
A pink and yellow scalloped flower appears on Top of the intersecting ribbons in the middle of the screen
showing the word
end.
